### The Image Component

Next.js's `next/image` extends the HTML `<img>` element with automatic optimization:

```jsx
import Image from 'next/image';

export default function Profile() {
  return (
    <Image
      src="/profile.jpg"
      alt="Profile picture"
      width={400}
      height={400}
    />
  );
}
```

### Benefits

- **Lazy Loading**: Images load only when they enter the viewport
- **Responsive Images**: Serves multiple sizes based on device
- **WebP/AVIF**: Modern formats are used automatically
- **Stability**: Prevents layout shift with explicit dimensions

### Placeholder and Blur

Use a blur-up placeholder while the image loads:

```jsx
import Image from 'next/image';
import myImage from '../public/photo.jpg';

export default function Photo() {
  return (
    <Image
      src={myImage}
      alt="Photo"
      placeholder="blur"
    />
  );
}
```

Local images support blur automatically. For remote images, provide a `blurDataURL`:

```jsx
<Image
  src="https://example.com/photo.jpg"
  alt="Remote"
  width={800}
  height={600}
  placeholder="blur"
  blurDataURL="data:image/webp;base64,..."
/>
```

### Remote Images

For external URLs, configure `next.config.js`:

```js
// next.config.js
module.exports = {
  images: {
    remotePatterns: [
      {
        protocol: 'https',
        hostname: 'images.unsplash.com',
      },
    ],
  },
};
```

### Priority and Loading

Use `priority` for above-the-fold images to skip lazy loading:

```jsx
<Image src="/hero.jpg" alt="Hero" fill priority />
```

### The sizes Prop

For fill images, use `sizes` to inform the browser about expected widths:

```jsx
<Image
  src="/grid-photo.jpg"
  alt="Grid"
  fill
  sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw, (max-width: 1200px) 50vw, 33vw"
/>
```

codeExample:
import Image from 'next/image';

export default function Gallery() {
  const images = [
    { src: '/photo1.jpg', alt: 'Photo 1' },
    { src: '/photo2.jpg', alt: 'Photo 2' },
  ];

  return (
    <div style={{ display: 'grid', gridTemplateColumns: '1fr 1fr' }}>
      {images.map((img) => (
        <Image
          key={img.src}
          src={img.src}
          alt={img.alt}
          width={600}
          height={400}
          placeholder="blur"
          blurDataURL="data:image/jpeg;base64,/9j/4AAQSkZJRg=="
        />
      ))}
    </div>
  );
}
